Hello Glenda,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix Technical Support. My name is Robert Rousselle and I'll be the engineer assisting you with this ticket.

I understand you are looking for the data retention settings in Netwrix Auditor and how to access the data as well. Below I've compiled some screenshots within Netwrix Auditor where you can locate these features.

All of these locations are under Settings from the Netwrix Auditor main dashboard. Once in settings we can find the following locations on the left pane:

Under Audit Database, we can modify Database retention settings located here -
[cid:image002.png@01DB9FFF.51C39290]

Under Long-Term Archive, we can modify the retention settings and where the audit data writes -
[cid:image003.png@01DB9FFF.51C39290]


Lastly, under Investigations, we can import past data from the Long-Term Archive (LTA) to investigate that data -
[cid:image004.png@01DB9FFF.51C39290]


For further insight into these settings, you can also reference these knowledgebase article here:
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/Auditor_10.7/page/Content/Auditor/Admin/Settings/AuditDatabase.htm

https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/Auditor_10.7/page/Content/Auditor/Admin/Settings/LongTermArchive.htm

https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/Auditor_10.7/page/Content/Auditor/Admin/Settings/Investigations.htm



I look forward to hearing from you with an update on if these steps resolved your issue. If you require further assistance and would like to request to schedule a remote session, please let me know and we can get that scheduled out.

Thank you!

TextBody:
Hello Glenda,
 
Thank you for contacting Netwrix Technical Support.
 
Activity Monitor has a 10-day retention period, which can be modified as needed. However, you also have access to enable the Archive and set it to a specific location under the Agent tab.
If the Archive was enabled from Activity Monitor, you can go to the location where it is set.
 
In NEA, if you Expend the File System and Expand FSAC System Scan, Expand Configure, and click Queries.
Click Query Properties and click Configure, you will see the Retention under the Scan Filters. 
 
Please let me know if you have any questions.
 
Thanks,

Hello Glenda,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix Technical Support.

Activity Monitor has a 10-day retention period, which can be modified as needed. However, you also have access to enable the Archive and set it to a specific location under the Agent tab.
If the Archive was enabled from Activity Monitor, you can go to the location where it is set.

In NEA, if you Expend the File System and Expand FSAC System Scan, Expand Configure, and click Queries.
Click Query Properties and click Configure, you will see the Retention under the Scan Filters.

Please let me know if you have any questions.

Hello Glenda,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix Technical Support.

Activity Monitor has a 10-day retention period, which can be modified as needed. However, you also have access to enable the Archive and set it to a specific location under the Agent tab.
If the Archive was enabled from Activity Monitor, you can go to the location where it is set.

In NEA, if you Expend the File System and Expand FSAC System Scan, Expand Configure, and click Queries.
Click Query Properties and click Configure, you will see the Retention under the Scan Filters.

Please let me know if you have any questions.

Thanks,

Subject: RE: [External]RE: [External]RE: [External]RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #440395 -  - [External]Data retained for auditing and archive data retrieval    [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0NSC2e:ref ]

TextBody:
Hi Glenda,
 
Thank you for your time today.
We reviewed the Activity Monitor in today's meeting, and everything looks fine.
 
We discuss the Disk Quota, which applies only to local disk usage. It allows you to archive files more often than once a day.
 
The retention period affects files no matter where they are located, locally or on a network drive.
When you enable Archiving, you want to increase the retention to the period you want to keep the archive, for a year or two years.
 
The Archived logs remain fully searchable via the Netwrix Activity Monitor Console. That means you can search for data from the Archive folder in Activity Monitor.
 
Please let me know if you have any questions.
 
Thanks,


Frantz Jean Baptiste

Hello Glenda,
 
Activity Monitor has a 10-day retention period, which can be modified as needed. However, you also have access to enable the Archive and set it to a specific location under the Agent tab.
If the Archive was enabled from Activity Monitor, you can go to the location where it is set.
 

 
In NEA, if you Expend the File System and Expand FSAC System Scan, Expand Configure, and click Queries.
Click Query Properties and click Configure, you will see the Retention under the Scan Filters.
